<subSubSection pageId="61" pageNumber="62" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="61.[151,1437,826,1141]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,826,852]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Coloration white with black spots, frons, and thorax ventrally black (
<figureCitation box="[1044,1128,826,852]" captionStart="FIGURE 36" captionStartId="64.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-21@64.[165,1422,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="FIGURE 36. Lichenodentix dentatithorax. A–B. Habitus in lateral and dorsal view. C–D. Head and pronotum in lateral and dorsal view. E. Cercus. F. Subgenital plate. (Photos A and B F. Domenico. Figs E–F after Costa-Lima &amp; Guitton, 1961)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876301/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
); base of fore femur brown. Head elongate with elevated fastigium, undulate margins, wide in both lateral and frontal view (
<figureCitation box="[1231,1369,862,889]" captionStart="FIGURE 36" captionStartId="64.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-21@64.[165,1422,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="FIGURE 36. Lichenodentix dentatithorax. A–B. Habitus in lateral and dorsal view. C–D. Head and pronotum in lateral and dorsal view. E. Cercus. F. Subgenital plate. (Photos A and B F. Domenico. Figs E–F after Costa-Lima &amp; Guitton, 1961)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876301/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Fig. 36A, C</figureCitation>
). Vertex with a granule or evagination at the margin of each eye. Antennae nodose. Pronotum elevated at rear end, with denticulations on rear margin and lateral edges of metazona (
<figureCitation box="[857,964,934,960]" captionStart="FIGURE 36" captionStartId="64.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-21@64.[165,1422,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="FIGURE 36. Lichenodentix dentatithorax. A–B. Habitus in lateral and dorsal view. C–D. Head and pronotum in lateral and dorsal view. E. Cercus. F. Subgenital plate. (Photos A and B F. Domenico. Figs E–F after Costa-Lima &amp; Guitton, 1961)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876301/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Fig. 36D</figureCitation>
). Tegmina apically broadened at the anal margin, costal margin curved (
<figureCitation box="[500,605,970,996]" captionStart="FIGURE 36" captionStartId="64.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-21@64.[165,1422,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="FIGURE 36. Lichenodentix dentatithorax. A–B. Habitus in lateral and dorsal view. C–D. Head and pronotum in lateral and dorsal view. E. Cercus. F. Subgenital plate. (Photos A and B F. Domenico. Figs E–F after Costa-Lima &amp; Guitton, 1961)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876301/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Fig. 36B</figureCitation>
). Spines on hind femora moderately broadened and flattened. Male cerci robust, with inner and outer branches similar in size and curving inward (
<figureCitation box="[985,1087,1006,1032]" captionStart="FIGURE 36" captionStartId="64.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-21@64.[165,1422,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="FIGURE 36. Lichenodentix dentatithorax. A–B. Habitus in lateral and dorsal view. C–D. Head and pronotum in lateral and dorsal view. E. Cercus. F. Subgenital plate. (Photos A and B F. Domenico. Figs E–F after Costa-Lima &amp; Guitton, 1961)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876301/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Fig. 36E</figureCitation>
). Male subgenital plate shorter than length of cerci (
<figureCitation box="[383,483,1042,1068]" captionStart="FIGURE 36" captionStartId="64.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-21@64.[165,1422,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="FIGURE 36. Lichenodentix dentatithorax. A–B. Habitus in lateral and dorsal view. C–D. Head and pronotum in lateral and dorsal view. E. Cercus. F. Subgenital plate. (Photos A and B F. Domenico. Figs E–F after Costa-Lima &amp; Guitton, 1961)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876301/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Fig. 36F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
